Author: Lauda
Title: ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê[‚ö°Ô∏èANN] [üî•LAUNCH] [NHCT] BLOCKCHAIN POWERED ECOSYSTEM FOR TOTAL HEALTH‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
Body: Blockchain Powered Ecosystem For Total Health  Website         Whitepaper            What is NHCT?  NHCT is a total health management platform that is built on the philosophy of preventive rather than reactive medical care. It uses blockchain to counter systemic issues that plague healthcare of today like high costs, data fragmentation & data security.  Why NHCT?  NHCT uses Blockchain to create a global, decentralized health & wellness ecosystem. Introduction of a distributed ledger helps NHCT facilitate: a) Enhanced data protection b) Frictionless data exchange c) Data Integrity by the use of smart contracts d) Incentivized engagement using Tokens  Our NHCT App  Being healthy means continuously working towards it via regular exercise, medical checkups and sometimes taking medicine when necessary. This involves coordination between various Health and Wellness providers and disciplined lifestyle.   NHCT Ecosystem   NHCT benefits all participants in the ecosystem:  Users are motivated to adhere to schedule and focus on their health and well-being. For every positive action, they are rewarded with tokens.  Payers benefit from reduced claims due to lower instances of health issues amongst the users.  Providers can obtain high-quality user-generated data through tokenized subsidies.    3-tier token architecture helps the NHCT system to reward users based on their involvement:  Wawa can be earned by making healthy choices and recording your activities.  Warma can be earned when activities are verified by others - like a marathon or a football game.  NHCT can be earned by uploading clinically verified data like medical reports. NHCT can then be used to pay doctors, insurers or even gym membership fee.       Awards & Accolades    Hult Prize - Winner 2014    RICH Cancer Innovation Challenge - Shortlisted among the Top 6 Startups    Community Battle of the ICOs - Winner CBOTI organized by Initial Coin List
